parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause extended stopping distances, loss of control, and accidents, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the vehicle shakes or vibrates when braking
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle
and the vehicle experiences unintended acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle is unable to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive wear on the brake rotors and pads can cause the brakes to fail, leading to extended stopping distances and accidents.
symptoms: The brake pads wear down excessively
the brake rotors are excessively worn
and the vehicle experiences vibrations or pulsations when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper motor can cause reduced visibility while driving, increasing the risk of accidents, especially in rainy or snowy conditions.
symptoms: wipers stop in the middle of the windshield
wipers continue to run after being turned off
burning smell or flames from the rear door panel.

The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
